1
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,615
You haven't stopped moving all night.

2
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:56,850
Your WeChat step count

3
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:58,084
must be over twenty thousand.

4
00:01:59,352 --> 00:02:00,320
I'm honestly scared.

5
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:01,554
The old gentleman

6
00:02:01,688 --> 00:02:02,255
really can't afford

7
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:03,123
any more setbacks now.

8
00:02:03,723 --> 00:02:04,991
We'll all keep a close eye on him.

9
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:05,992
Don't worry.

10
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:12,799
When I first started working,

11
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:14,734
during my very first week,

12
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:15,768
I made a terrible mistake.

13
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:17,370
The catheter from a PICC line

14
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:17,670
broke off

15
00:02:17,670 --> 00:02:18,671
inside the patient's body,

16
00:02:19,005 --> 00:02:20,473
and I didn't notice it right away.

17
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:23,943
The fragment drifted through the vessels,

18
00:02:24,077 --> 00:02:24,944
which was extremely dangerous.

19
00:02:25,678 --> 00:02:26,312
What happened after that?

20
00:02:26,946 --> 00:02:27,447
Later,

21
00:02:27,714 --> 00:02:29,249
the patient had to undergo major surgery

22
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,316
and suffered a great deal

23
00:02:30,683 --> 00:02:31,951
before the catheter could be removed.

24
00:02:32,318 --> 00:02:33,520
Fortunately,

25
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,387
the patient's prognosis was good.

26
00:02:34,687 --> 00:02:35,688
The patient and family

27
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:36,890
also forgave us.

28
00:02:37,891 --> 00:02:38,591
I still remember

29
00:02:38,591 --> 00:02:39,526
what she said to me then.

30
00:02:39,559 --> 00:02:40,360
She said,

31
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:41,427
"You've just started working.

32
00:02:41,895 --> 00:02:43,029
Newcomers are bound to make mistakes.

33
00:02:43,396 --> 00:02:44,864
But

34
00:02:45,398 --> 00:02:45,865
the earlier you make one,

35
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:47,133
the earlier you must learn from it,

36
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:48,401
so you don't make

37
00:02:49,135 --> 00:02:50,670
an even bigger,

38
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:52,105
irreversible mistake later."

39
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:54,073
Head Nurse.

40
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:55,875
I'll never forget

41
00:02:56,376 --> 00:02:57,410
the lesson from this time.

42
00:02:58,611 --> 00:03:00,213
In clinical work,

43
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,348
many of our hardest lessons

44
00:03:02,949 --> 00:03:04,150
come from patients.

45
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:06,586
Every profession has a beginner stage.

46
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:08,755
But ours is too special.

47
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:10,223
Even the smallest

48
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,559
mistake on our part

49
00:03:12,725 --> 00:03:13,526
can be enormous

50
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:14,727
for a patient.

51
00:03:15,562 --> 00:03:16,829
Remember the lesson.

52
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:18,865
Turn guilt into action.

53
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,433
Show more care

54
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:21,668
in your daily work,

55
00:03:22,001 --> 00:03:23,069
and work twice as hard.

56
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:30,143
Ms. Jiang.

57
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:31,144
I'm sorry.

58
00:03:32,478 --> 00:03:33,846
Mr. Peng suffered because of me.

59
00:03:35,081 --> 00:03:36,149
I'm truly sorry.

60
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:37,750
This was my mistake.

61
00:03:38,785 --> 00:03:39,686
I really was

62
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:40,787
too hasty at the time.

63
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:43,823
My technique wasn't good enough.

64
00:03:43,823 --> 00:03:44,791
I won't make excuses.

65
00:03:45,224 --> 00:03:45,725
I'm sorry.

66
00:03:48,761 --> 00:03:49,429
Ms. Jiang.

67
00:03:50,263 --> 00:03:52,398
Xiao Du is still in specialty training.

68
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,133
He made an operational error,

69
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:55,368
and as his supervising physician,

70
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,369
I bear primary responsibility.

71
00:03:57,203 --> 00:03:58,471
So I want to formally apologize

72
00:03:58,471 --> 00:03:59,272
to you again.

73
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:01,074
I'm truly sorry.

74
00:04:05,044 --> 00:04:06,012
Our department

75
00:04:06,279 --> 00:04:07,347
has deducted one month's

76
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:08,448
performance bonus from Xiao Du.

77
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:10,650
I will also strengthen

78
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:11,784
his training.

79
00:04:12,318 --> 00:04:13,152
More importantly,

80
00:04:13,286 --> 00:04:15,121
we'll monitor Mr. Peng more closely

81
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:17,156
and make sure this never happens again.

82
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:24,264
Poor Mr. Peng.

83
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:26,165
He was already so seriously ill,

84
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:27,734
and now

85
00:04:28,635 --> 00:04:30,269
he's suffered even more.

86
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:36,209
Tell us,

87
00:04:37,276 --> 00:04:38,544
is there anything else you need?

88
00:04:39,912 --> 00:04:41,147
We'll do our best to accommodate you.

89
00:04:49,555 --> 00:04:50,957
I really want to blame you.

90
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:52,792
But

91
00:04:53,793 --> 00:04:55,595
the informed consent form said

92
00:04:56,229 --> 00:04:57,997
these complications can occur.

93
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:00,466
And you already

94
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,601
warned me

95
00:05:02,669 --> 00:05:04,203
that prolonged intubation without tracheostomy

96
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:07,440
could lead to complications.

97
00:05:12,011 --> 00:05:14,447
Mr. Peng suffered this time

98
00:05:18,551 --> 00:05:19,986
partly because of my choice too.

99
00:05:32,432 --> 00:05:33,333
I won't pursue it.

100
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:38,771
I don't have any other demands.

101
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:48,514
But

102
00:05:49,749 --> 00:05:50,283
Dr. Fang,

103
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:51,584
I still want to ask:

104
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:53,486
if we don't do a tracheostomy,

105
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:56,522
will Mr. Peng get better?

106
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:01,761
All I can say is,

107
00:06:03,563 --> 00:06:05,198
if we simply maintain the status quo

108
00:06:05,231 --> 00:06:06,332
and do nothing,

109
00:06:08,234 --> 00:06:09,469
Mr. Peng will face

110
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:11,804
even more

111
00:06:11,804 --> 00:06:12,672
difficult challenges.

112
00:06:13,806 --> 00:06:14,440
So

113
00:06:15,408 --> 00:06:16,042
regarding the tracheostomy,

114
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,443
I'd still like you

115
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,644
to think it over carefully.

116
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:25,885
We've paused the sedatives

117
00:06:25,918 --> 00:06:26,853
to let him wake for a while.

118
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:27,887
Try communicating with him.

119
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:29,489
He can nod or shake his head,

120
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:30,523
or write

121
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:31,391
on a board to answer you.

122
00:06:39,632 --> 00:06:40,400
Mr. Peng.

123
00:06:42,335 --> 00:06:43,136
I'm here.

124
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:45,371
It's me.

125
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:51,878
Mr. Peng.

126
00:06:52,311 --> 00:06:53,146
Listen to me.

127
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,515
Don't panic.

128
00:06:56,048 --> 00:06:56,682
The doctors are all

129
00:06:56,716 --> 00:06:58,117
trying to help you.

130
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:00,953
To help you breathe better,

131
00:07:01,487 --> 00:07:02,088
they need to

132
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:04,757
open your trachea.

133
00:07:05,825 --> 00:07:06,926
D-Don't get agitated.

134
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,628
Listen to me. I remember.

135
00:07:09,729 --> 00:07:11,197
I remember our agreement.

136
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:17,303
But I still want to ask you:

137
00:07:19,038 --> 00:07:19,572
why don't we

138
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,809
listen to the doctors, okay?

139
00:07:44,263 --> 00:07:44,964
Mr. Peng Mao,

140
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,601
based on your current condition,

141
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:50,670
we have to perform a tracheostomy.

142
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:52,872
Of course, we also respect

143
00:07:52,905 --> 00:07:53,606
your own wishes.

144
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:01,013
If you agree,

145
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:02,482
put a check mark here.

146
00:08:03,182 --> 00:08:03,616
If you don't,

147
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:05,084
put an X.

148
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:51,731
Mr. Peng.

149
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:52,965
Listen to me.

150
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:55,534
Only by opening the airway

151
00:08:55,968 --> 00:08:57,236
do you have a chance.

152
00:08:58,638 --> 00:09:00,172
What if one day,

153
00:09:01,574 --> 00:09:02,475
you can't even

154
00:09:02,475 --> 00:09:03,409
speak anymore?

155
00:09:04,343 --> 00:09:05,144
Then how would you

156
00:09:05,144 --> 00:09:06,245
express your wishes?

157
00:09:07,847 --> 00:09:09,882
We agreed in advance.

158
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:12,051
But I heard

159
00:09:12,585 --> 00:09:13,886
the closer someone is to death,

160
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:16,289
the stronger the instinct to live.

161
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:18,724
What if, by then,

162
00:09:19,792 --> 00:09:21,227
we change our minds?

163
00:09:22,495 --> 00:09:22,962
Then

164
00:09:23,963 --> 00:09:25,131
let's agree on a signal.

165
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:26,666
When that time comes,

166
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,601
I'll blink three times.

167
00:09:29,835 --> 00:09:30,970
You'll know what I mean:

168
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:32,572
don't let me

169
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:33,472
keep suffering like this.

170
00:09:35,007 --> 00:09:36,208
Even if I can't speak then,

171
00:09:36,976 --> 00:09:38,144
I should still be able to blink.

172
00:09:41,213 --> 00:09:41,614
Then

173
00:09:42,481 --> 00:09:43,349
blink for me now.

174
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:52,892
No.

175
00:09:54,026 --> 00:09:55,494
Listen to me.

176
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:58,030
Don't get agitated.

177
00:09:58,064 --> 00:09:58,531
Ms. Jiang.

178
00:09:59,231 --> 00:09:59,732
Ms. Jiang.

179
00:10:00,232 --> 00:10:01,334
I'm going to sedate him.

180
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:04,637
Midazolam, four milliliters per hour.

181
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:06,572
Don't get agitated.

182
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:08,307
Please don't get too upset.

183
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:09,976
Don't get agitated.

184
00:10:12,478 --> 00:10:14,547
I remember. I remember.

185
00:10:20,086 --> 00:10:20,720
It's all right.

186
00:10:21,354 --> 00:10:22,254
It's okay. It's okay.

187
00:10:26,158 --> 00:10:27,627
I knew it.

188
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:31,430
I knew it.

189
00:10:35,434 --> 00:10:37,236
I haven't forgotten.

190
00:10:38,771 --> 00:10:41,907
I haven't forgotten our agreement.

191
00:10:43,042 --> 00:10:45,745
I just can't bear to let go.

192
00:10:48,681 --> 00:10:50,983
I can't bear it.

193
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:13,472
Ms. Jiang.

194
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:16,509
May I speak with you for a moment?

195
00:11:22,648 --> 00:11:23,282
Ms. Jiang.

196
00:11:23,749 --> 00:11:24,850
Two weeks

197
00:11:25,051 --> 00:11:26,519
is basically the limit

198
00:11:26,552 --> 00:11:27,253
for endotracheal intubation.

199
00:11:28,554 --> 00:11:29,388
If you're certain

200
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:30,956
you don't want a tracheostomy for Mr. Peng,

201
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:32,224
then soon

202
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:34,093
I plan to switch him to nasotracheal intubation.

203
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:37,930
But nasotracheal intubation

204
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:39,799
is painful too.

205
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:42,001
And his infection

206
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,402
may still worsen.

207
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:50,309
I understand.

208
00:11:52,244 --> 00:11:53,245
Thank you for all your work.

209
00:11:59,518 --> 00:11:59,752
Remove it.

210
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,189
I understand that Mr. Peng

211
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:04,690
wants to live with dignity.

212
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:05,958
But if—

213
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:06,792
Dr. Fang.

214
00:12:07,426 --> 00:12:08,828
Mr. Peng and I have been together

215
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:10,563
for thirty full years.

216
00:12:13,332 --> 00:12:14,834
In all those years, it seems

217
00:12:14,867 --> 00:12:16,368
we were never apart for even a day.

218
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:18,070
We are partners,

219
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,473
and, more than anything,

220
00:12:21,674 --> 00:12:22,775
each other's closest confidants.

221
00:12:23,976 --> 00:12:25,878
We lived together,

222
00:12:26,212 --> 00:12:26,846
and also wandered together

223
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:27,913
through the ocean of literature.

224
00:12:29,615 --> 00:12:31,550
Over these thirty years,

225
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:34,053
we've walked hand in hand

226
00:12:39,792 --> 00:12:41,227
through the scenery of many lifetimes.

227
00:12:43,529 --> 00:12:44,930
I understand him completely.

228
00:12:49,802 --> 00:12:51,470
So even though

229
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,549
it's incredibly hard to let go,

230
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:05,584
I still respect

231
00:13:06,385 --> 00:13:07,086
his decision.

232
00:13:08,921 --> 00:13:09,321
Yes.

233
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:11,557
It is wonderful.

234
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,363
Actually,

235
00:13:17,396 --> 00:13:18,464
our journey

236
00:13:19,431 --> 00:13:20,466
wasn't easy either.

237
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,235
We went from teacher and student to partners,

238
00:13:23,903 --> 00:13:26,238
and carried a great deal of misunderstanding and criticism.

239
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:28,707
Because of that, Mr. Peng lost

240
00:13:28,707 --> 00:13:30,376
every chance of administrative promotion.

241
00:13:30,743 --> 00:13:33,078
He remained an ordinary teacher all his life.

242
00:13:34,213 --> 00:13:35,948
His health was poor and he needed care,

243
00:13:36,949 --> 00:13:39,485
so I also gave up many career opportunities.

244
00:13:40,186 --> 00:13:41,353
But what comforts me is

245
00:13:42,054 --> 00:13:43,355
that we were always certain of each other

246
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:45,491
and never regretted it.

247
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:49,128
I asked both of you here today

248
00:13:49,562 --> 00:13:50,563
mainly to discuss

249
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:52,031
Mr. Peng Mao's family.

250
00:13:52,631 --> 00:13:54,333
The Medical Affairs Office has repeatedly

251
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,601
tried to negotiate a settlement,

252
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:56,836
but the family ultimately

253
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:57,870
refused mediation.

254
00:13:58,637 --> 00:14:00,372
They insist

255
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:01,874
on pursuing legal action

256
00:14:02,641 --> 00:14:03,876
and are asking the hospital

257
00:14:04,476 --> 00:14:05,477
to hold both

258
00:14:05,477 --> 00:14:06,312
of your departments responsible.

259
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:08,747
She's really that determined?

260
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:11,884
I heard Mr. Peng

261
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:12,985
developed a pneumothorax from the puncture,

262
00:14:13,986 --> 00:14:15,955
yet she didn't hold the ICU

263
00:14:15,988 --> 00:14:17,823
or Du Wenzheng responsible.

264
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:19,191
She seems quite reasonable.

265
00:14:21,327 --> 00:14:21,827
Director Zhou,

266
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:24,530
why don't your side step forward

267
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:25,865
and apologize to her?

268
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:27,866
It's best to turn a major issue

269
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:29,335
into a minor one.

270
00:14:32,238 --> 00:14:33,172
Our diagnostic and treatment process

271
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:34,039
was evidence-based.

272
00:14:34,506 --> 00:14:35,441
We just need to cooperate with the procedure.

273
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:36,842
There's no need

274
00:14:36,842 --> 00:14:37,843
to apologize simply for the sake of apologizing.

275
00:14:39,011 --> 00:14:39,945
I respect her decision.

276
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:45,084
The family also said

277
00:14:45,584 --> 00:14:47,086
that if the hospital believes

278
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:48,687
the doctors' actions

279
00:14:48,854 --> 00:14:49,855
were appropriate,

280
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:52,424
then they'll wait for the court's ruling.

281
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:00,266
I'm telling you,

282
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:01,033
if I were Ms. Jiang,

283
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:01,967
I'd ignore everything else

284
00:15:02,034 --> 00:15:03,135
and have the tracheostomy done directly.

285
00:15:03,435 --> 00:15:04,470
What if there were still a miracle?

286
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:06,672
That's easy for you to say.

287
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:07,606
Do you think Ms. Jiang

288
00:15:07,706 --> 00:15:08,974
can bear to let him go?

289
00:15:09,608 --> 00:15:10,709
And everyone

290
00:15:10,909 --> 00:15:12,144
has the right to decide

291
00:15:12,144 --> 00:15:13,479
how they leave this world.

292
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,347
No matter how reluctant loved ones are,

293
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:17,716
they can only respect that choice.

294
00:15:19,885 --> 00:15:21,053
People like Mr. Peng

295
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:21,787
and Du Yan

296
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:23,055
are so hard to read.

297
00:15:23,322 --> 00:15:24,356
They leave me completely at a loss.

298
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:28,027
Du Yan's condition

299
00:15:28,027 --> 00:15:28,927
has stabilized somewhat.

300
00:15:29,161 --> 00:15:30,562
Also considering the financial burden,

301
00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:31,196
we can begin weaning him

302
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:31,830
from ECMO.

303
00:15:32,331 --> 00:15:33,465
But the underlying disease remains.

304
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:35,434
This improvement is only temporary.

305
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:37,836
We saved him this time,

306
00:15:38,404 --> 00:15:39,305
but next time

307
00:15:39,305 --> 00:15:40,005
he may not be so lucky.

308
00:15:40,606 --> 00:15:41,974
We've only returned to square one.

309
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:44,143
He still needs surgery.

310
00:15:45,010 --> 00:15:45,544
As for a donor heart,

311
00:15:45,544 --> 00:15:46,912
there's been no news.

312
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:48,814
So the most direct and effective option

313
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:50,316
is still an artificial heart.

314
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:52,885
You've always known

315
00:15:52,885 --> 00:15:53,719
Du Yan's position.

316
00:15:54,086 --> 00:15:55,654
I'm worried that after ECMO withdrawal,

317
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:57,589
he'll remain just as determined.

318
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:02,628
What are we supposed to do then?

319
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,064
He may not talk much,

320
00:16:05,831 --> 00:16:07,566
but that child is stubborn.

321
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:08,934
Otherwise,

322
00:16:08,934 --> 00:16:09,802
we wouldn't have sent him there.

323
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:12,638
Whatever we say,

324
00:16:12,671 --> 00:16:14,006
he never listens.

325
00:16:14,673 --> 00:16:16,275
You keep saying he never listens.

326
00:16:17,209 --> 00:16:17,843
But what about you?

327
00:16:19,044 --> 00:16:20,512
Have you ever listened to him?

328
00:16:20,913 --> 00:16:21,480
Your child

329
00:16:21,513 --> 00:16:22,614
refused the artificial heart.

330
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:23,649
Couldn't you see

331
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:25,284
that he was using his life to fight you?

332
00:16:27,186 --> 00:16:28,754
We know we were wrong.

333
00:16:29,521 --> 00:16:29,989
Doctor,

334
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:31,824
please help us persuade him.

335
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,625
As long as he agrees to surgery,

336
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:35,728
he can do whatever he wants from now on.

337
00:16:36,362 --> 00:16:37,863
We'll go along with anything.

338
00:16:40,032 --> 00:16:41,800
As long as he lives.

339
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:52,644
What do we do, Dr. Fang?

340
00:16:53,645 --> 00:16:55,414
His parents are no help at all.

341
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:08,827
Dahuo.

342
00:17:12,331 --> 00:17:13,065
Why are you here?

343
00:17:13,632 --> 00:17:14,133
I said

344
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:15,200
I'd come see you in a couple of days.

345
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:18,670
You two talk.

346
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:19,772
We'll be next door.

347
00:17:20,005 --> 00:17:20,706
Call if you need anything.

348
00:17:27,513 --> 00:17:28,080
How are you?

349
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:33,352
I didn't want you to see me

350
00:17:34,586 --> 00:17:35,654
like this.

351
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:38,290
Fine.

352
00:17:40,025 --> 00:17:40,793
Then I won't come again.

353
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:45,230
But I'll wait for you

354
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:48,133
to come find me.

355
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:54,773
Do you remember this place?

356
00:18:15,727 --> 00:18:16,128
Let's go.

357
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:18,330
Where?

358
00:18:19,364 --> 00:18:19,765
Run.

359
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:20,866
Get out of here.

360
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:21,800
Are you crazy?

361
00:18:23,001 --> 00:18:23,969
What if the instructors catch us?

362
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:27,806
Forget them.

363
00:18:28,407 --> 00:18:28,774
Come with me.

364
00:18:40,252 --> 00:18:40,486
Go.

365
00:18:42,988 --> 00:18:43,355
Hurry.

366
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:47,493
Quick.

367
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:53,732
Go.

368
00:18:58,504 --> 00:18:58,837
Go.

369
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:11,717
What are you doing?

370
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:12,985
I'm looking for the mark.

371
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:23,695
Found it.

372
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:24,329
Jin Miao.

373
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:27,199
This is the place.

374
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:28,667
Look.

375
00:19:29,434 --> 00:19:30,235
I made a mark here.

376
00:19:31,637 --> 00:19:32,571
What kind of mess did you draw?

377
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:34,773
Keep going forward.

378
00:19:35,207 --> 00:19:35,908
After walking for a while,

379
00:19:36,241 --> 00:19:37,209
we'll reach a road.

380
00:19:38,076 --> 00:19:39,411
We can hitch a ride and escape home.

381
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,514
You found the route,

382
00:19:43,715 --> 00:19:44,349
then came back?

383
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:45,050
Of course.

384
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:46,952
I had to take you with me.

385
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:49,955
Metal, wood, water, fire, earth—we agreed.

386
00:19:50,389 --> 00:19:51,123
We can't split up.

387
00:19:55,627 --> 00:19:56,395
Come on. Hurry.

388
00:19:56,495 --> 00:19:56,762
Okay.

389
00:20:06,104 --> 00:20:06,805
How are you?

390
00:20:17,849 --> 00:20:18,283
Jin Miao.

391
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:19,318
Stop! Don't run!

392
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,120
I can't go on.

393
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:23,689
I'll stop them.

394
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:24,823
You go first.

395
00:20:28,327 --> 00:20:28,894
Jin Miao.

396
00:20:33,131 --> 00:20:33,732
Come find me after you get out.

397
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:46,478
You told me before

398
00:20:48,146 --> 00:20:49,014
that the academy had been demolished

399
00:20:50,649 --> 00:20:51,917
and you wanted to see what it looks like now.

400
00:20:53,552 --> 00:20:54,086
I've been there.

401
00:20:56,455 --> 00:20:57,155
It's now

402
00:20:57,256 --> 00:20:58,323
a field of rapeseed flowers.

403
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:01,226
Lots of people go there to take photos.

404
00:21:03,295 --> 00:21:03,962
But they don't know

405
00:21:03,996 --> 00:21:05,564
there's still a forest behind the hill.

406
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:10,435
Two people once

407
00:21:13,038 --> 00:21:13,805
wandered into that forest

408
00:21:13,839 --> 00:21:15,040
by accident.

409
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:20,512
Even knowing it was dangerous,

410
00:21:22,681 --> 00:21:24,216
they were still willing to break through together.

411
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:27,753
Dahuo.

412
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:30,555
Let's play a game.

413
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:33,892
I put your birthday present

414
00:21:35,694 --> 00:21:36,962
in that forest.

415
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:46,471
When you get better,

416
00:21:50,175 --> 00:21:50,876
go find it yourself.

417
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:07,993
What age are we in?

418
00:22:09,227 --> 00:22:09,828
You're still playing

419
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:11,263
children's treasure hunts?

420
00:22:12,264 --> 00:22:12,964
You scared?

421
00:22:13,765 --> 00:22:14,166
Kid.

422
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:30,849
Jin Miao asked me to give you this.

423
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:39,958
He's my only friend.

424
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:43,995
I had planned

425
00:22:45,464 --> 00:22:46,932
to say goodbye to him and then...

426
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:49,968
I know.

427
00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:52,871
I know how suffocating

428
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:54,005
your life used to be.

429
00:22:55,073 --> 00:22:56,408
And I know how badly you wanted

430
00:22:56,508 --> 00:22:57,409
to escape your parents' control,

431
00:22:58,410 --> 00:22:59,010
even if it meant

432
00:22:59,111 --> 00:23:00,612
using your life to resist them.

433
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,384
I'm tired, Dr. Fang.

434
00:23:08,954 --> 00:23:09,654
Now I don't even

435
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:11,189
have the strength to fight anymore.

436
00:23:12,591 --> 00:23:14,292
My life has become airtight.

437
00:23:15,427 --> 00:23:17,162
This is the only path left.

438
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:20,365
To return everything they gave me,

439
00:23:21,466 --> 00:23:22,534
including

440
00:23:25,470 --> 00:23:26,505
my life.

441
00:23:27,606 --> 00:23:28,306
Who said

442
00:23:28,306 --> 00:23:29,641
this is your only path?

443
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:32,844
You're already eighteen.

444
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:34,846
You're an adult who can choose

445
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,414
your own treatment plan.

446
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:39,951
You can live

447
00:23:39,951 --> 00:23:41,486
in the way you want,

448
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,255
and choose the road you want to take.

449
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:49,528
If you don't like

450
00:23:49,528 --> 00:23:50,829
the pigeon soup your mother brings,

451
00:23:51,329 --> 00:23:52,030
then don't drink it.

452
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:53,765
If you don't want to forgive them,

453
00:23:53,965 --> 00:23:54,766
you don't have to force yourself.

454
00:23:56,368 --> 00:23:57,869
You can go find Jin Miao

455
00:23:59,304 --> 00:23:59,838
and continue

456
00:23:59,905 --> 00:24:01,406
your story of metal, wood, water, fire, and earth.

457
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:05,110
You still have a very long road ahead.

458
00:24:06,478 --> 00:24:07,679
Don't give up on yourself so easily.

459
00:24:08,513 --> 00:24:09,614
I believe you can

460
00:24:09,714 --> 00:24:11,016
find your own direction.

461
00:24:38,543 --> 00:24:39,511
He agreed.

462
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:51,156
Director Lin.

463
00:24:54,392 --> 00:24:55,694
You'll perform the surgery.

464
00:25:00,632 --> 00:25:01,766
There should be

465
00:25:02,033 --> 00:25:03,168
a consultation tomorrow about the plan.

466
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:04,736
I'll let you know then.

467
00:25:30,395 --> 00:25:30,896
Director Zhou.

468
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:33,031
Dr. Fang is amazing.

469
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:34,466
Du Yan is such a stubborn kid,

470
00:25:34,566 --> 00:25:35,066
yet she still found a way

471
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:36,034
to change his mind.

472
00:25:37,469 --> 00:25:38,370
I also heard her say

473
00:25:38,503 --> 00:25:39,638
Director Lin will be the lead surgeon.

474
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:41,306
Now Du Yan's surgery

475
00:25:41,406 --> 00:25:41,907
has real hope.

476
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:47,612
Lin Yi's surgery

477
00:25:47,679 --> 00:25:48,547
should be ending soon.

478
00:25:48,813 --> 00:25:49,548
Let's wait for him.

479
00:25:58,123 --> 00:25:58,790
You brought an extra model?

480
00:25:59,391 --> 00:25:59,724
Yes.

481
00:26:00,158 --> 00:26:01,993
The other one is an overseas product.

482
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,361
It only entered the domestic market this year.

483
00:26:03,528 --> 00:26:04,729
Mr. Qin asked me to bring it

484
00:26:04,996 --> 00:26:06,398
for Director Zhou and Director Lin

485
00:26:06,431 --> 00:26:07,165
to consider as well.

486
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:12,003
I'll urge him.

487
00:26:20,011 --> 00:26:20,445
Director Zhou.

488
00:26:21,479 --> 00:26:22,080
Director Sheng.

489
00:26:23,481 --> 00:26:24,049
Director Sheng.

490
00:26:24,316 --> 00:26:24,749
Manager Ouyang.

491
00:26:25,317 --> 00:26:25,784
Let's begin.

492
00:26:33,792 --> 00:26:35,193
I'll be the lead surgeon

493
00:26:35,627 --> 00:26:36,227
for Du Yan's artificial-heart operation.

494
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:40,765
Any objections?

495
00:26:49,874 --> 00:26:50,475
Manager Ouyang.

496
00:26:52,110 --> 00:26:52,644
Go ahead.

497
00:26:56,114 --> 00:26:57,549
We've prepared two products.

498
00:27:01,353 --> 00:27:02,053
The first is domestic.

499
00:27:02,053 --> 00:27:02,921
What's the situation?

500
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:04,823
It's larger,

501
00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:06,758
but provides relatively stronger output.

502
00:27:06,992 --> 00:27:08,393
It's more suitable for critically ill patients

503
00:27:08,426 --> 00:27:09,728
who need greater circulatory support.

504
00:27:10,228 --> 00:27:11,329
The other

505
00:27:11,329 --> 00:27:12,263
is a Spanish product.

506
00:27:12,564 --> 00:27:13,932
It has been on the overseas market

507
00:27:13,932 --> 00:27:14,466
for several years

508
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:16,067
and only entered China this year.

509
00:27:16,434 --> 00:27:17,202
Its advantage

510
00:27:17,235 --> 00:27:18,036
is its smaller size.

511
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:20,372
I remember Du Yan

512
00:27:20,372 --> 00:27:21,272
is relatively thin.

513
00:27:21,606 --> 00:27:22,641
Wouldn't this

514
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:24,309
smaller and lighter model

515
00:27:24,342 --> 00:27:25,243
suit him better?

516
00:27:26,277 --> 00:27:26,878
Let's use this one.

517
00:27:30,415 --> 00:27:30,949
Director Sheng.

518
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:32,117
Du Yan

519
00:27:32,384 --> 00:27:33,485
looks thin,

520
00:27:33,785 --> 00:27:34,853
but he's tall,

521
00:27:35,186 --> 00:27:36,388
so his body weight is still considerable.

522
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:37,689
Once he recovers,

523
00:27:37,689 --> 00:27:38,523
the amount of support

524
00:27:38,556 --> 00:27:39,290
he'll need will also be substantial.

525
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:40,158
And he has only just

526
00:27:40,191 --> 00:27:40,792
been weaned from ECMO.

527
00:27:40,959 --> 00:27:41,760
His condition is critical.

528
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:43,762
The higher-flow domestic pump

529
00:27:44,062 --> 00:27:44,996
can support him better

530
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:46,264
through this immediate danger.

531
00:27:48,566 --> 00:27:49,200
Besides,

532
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:50,168
he's still young.

533
00:27:51,036 --> 00:27:51,703
He has a chance to wait

534
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:52,604
for a heart transplant,

535
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,006
though donor hearts are hard to come by.

536
00:27:55,874 --> 00:27:56,975
Precisely because he's young,

537
00:27:57,442 --> 00:27:59,110
he'll probably need the artificial heart

538
00:27:59,244 --> 00:28:00,912
for longer

539
00:28:01,046 --> 00:28:01,646
than an elderly patient.

540
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:03,248
Then why not choose

541
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:04,349
the more portable model

542
00:28:04,783 --> 00:28:05,784
that would better support

543
00:28:05,784 --> 00:28:06,951
his future life?

544
00:28:11,556 --> 00:28:12,157
Director Zhou,

545
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:13,958
aren't you considering his future?

546
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:18,163
If he can't survive

547
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:18,997
the immediate crisis,

548
00:28:19,564 --> 00:28:20,865
what future is there to discuss?

549
00:28:21,666 --> 00:28:22,767
This new imported device

550
00:28:23,001 --> 00:28:23,835
doesn't provide enough flow

551
00:28:23,835 --> 00:28:25,403
for a critically ill patient

552
00:28:26,171 --> 00:28:26,905
and lacks sufficient

553
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:27,972
domestic clinical data.

554
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:29,874
I'm the lead surgeon.

555
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:32,310
I know which device to use.

556
00:28:33,445 --> 00:28:33,878
Director Zhou,

557
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:36,347
are you planning to pick up

558
00:28:36,848 --> 00:28:37,916
a cardiac surgeon's scalpel?

559
00:28:39,984 --> 00:28:41,319
If that's your attitude, Director Sheng,

560
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:43,288
is there any point

561
00:28:43,288 --> 00:28:44,122
in holding this consultation?

562
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:45,290
To be blunt,

563
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:47,692
Cardiac Surgery's operations

564
00:28:48,126 --> 00:28:50,095
never required

565
00:28:50,495 --> 00:28:51,496
Cardiology's involvement in the first place.

566
00:29:07,846 --> 00:29:08,480
All right. I understand.

567
00:29:12,383 --> 00:29:14,185
Xiao Du said Sheng Nian

568
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:15,153
temporarily assigned Lin Yi

569
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:15,987
an emergency operation.

570
00:29:15,987 --> 00:29:16,688
He couldn't get through to him.

571
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:21,593
Director Sheng is going to do this surgery.

572
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:23,561
You definitely didn't know that.

573
00:29:24,062 --> 00:29:24,596
No.

574
00:29:25,530 --> 00:29:26,598
Then did Qin Xiong know?

575
00:29:28,466 --> 00:29:29,400
I'm not sure.

576
00:29:30,034 --> 00:29:31,469
But when I left today,

577
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:32,971
I had only prepared the domestic brand.

578
00:29:33,638 --> 00:29:34,405
Just before I left,

579
00:29:34,472 --> 00:29:35,373
he suddenly stopped me

580
00:29:35,507 --> 00:29:36,808
and told me to bring

581
00:29:36,808 --> 00:29:37,408
the Spanish product too.

582
00:29:37,976 --> 00:29:39,010
As far as I know,

583
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:40,745
that manufacturer

584
00:29:40,845 --> 00:29:41,679
has been looking for a chance

585
00:29:41,679 --> 00:29:42,847
to complete a procedure in China.

586
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:45,150
At present,

587
00:29:45,316 --> 00:29:46,718
they have no domestic use cases.

588
00:29:47,285 --> 00:29:47,685
None.

589
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,654
If it's used this time,

590
00:29:49,654 --> 00:29:50,788
it will be the first case in China.

591
00:29:51,556 --> 00:29:52,824
And if I remember correctly,

592
00:29:53,158 --> 00:29:54,826
wouldn't it also be Dongli Hospital's

593
00:29:54,893 --> 00:29:56,327
first artificial-heart operation?

594
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:00,632
Put together,

595
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,333
that can't be a coincidence.

596
00:30:04,936 --> 00:30:06,171
In Du Yan's current condition,

597
00:30:06,671 --> 00:30:07,438
the more important thing

598
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:08,773
is getting him through

599
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:09,674
the immediate crisis.

600
00:30:10,575 --> 00:30:11,943
The domestic artificial heart

601
00:30:12,110 --> 00:30:13,912
clearly matches the data better.

602
00:30:14,445 --> 00:30:15,280
Director Sheng couldn't possibly

603
00:30:15,313 --> 00:30:16,047
be unaware of that.

604
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:17,949
Right.

605
00:30:18,349 --> 00:30:19,884
Some medical decisions

606
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:20,952
aren't made

607
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:22,253
solely for the patient's sake.

608
00:30:23,188 --> 00:30:24,088
Dongli's first.

609
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:25,023
China's first.

610
00:30:25,156 --> 00:30:26,157
Put those two together

611
00:30:26,558 --> 00:30:27,959
and the publicity alone is enough.

612
00:30:37,635 --> 00:30:38,069
What is it?

613
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:38,970
Why did you call me here so urgently?

614
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:44,008
Why didn't you tell me

615
00:30:44,108 --> 00:30:45,176
you couldn't attend Du Yan's consultation?

616
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:46,477
I was operating.

617
00:30:46,744 --> 00:30:47,312
You still could have

618
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:48,680
sent me a message.

619
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:49,948
You left us

620
00:30:50,048 --> 00:30:51,649
completely unprepared for Director Sheng.

621
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:53,151
I didn't know he'd go either.

622
00:30:57,088 --> 00:30:57,555
Lin Yi.

623
00:30:58,756 --> 00:30:59,691
As for Du Yan's surgery,

624
00:30:59,724 --> 00:31:00,925
I still want you to perform it.

625
00:31:05,263 --> 00:31:05,730
Why?

626
00:31:07,131 --> 00:31:08,166
Director Sheng chose

627
00:31:08,199 --> 00:31:09,000
an overseas product.

628
00:31:09,334 --> 00:31:10,668
But my brother and I both believe

629
00:31:10,835 --> 00:31:11,736
the domestic one

630
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,438
better suits Du Yan's current condition.

631
00:31:14,005 --> 00:31:14,505
He has only just

632
00:31:14,505 --> 00:31:15,406
been weaned from ECMO.

633
00:31:15,773 --> 00:31:16,841
Director Sheng is the lead surgeon.

634
00:31:17,108 --> 00:31:17,909
He has his own reasons

635
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:18,743
for choosing that product.

636
00:31:18,910 --> 00:31:20,245
But the one he chose

637
00:31:20,345 --> 00:31:21,479
has only just entered China

638
00:31:21,613 --> 00:31:22,647
and has never been used here.

639
00:31:23,348 --> 00:31:24,916
We both think he put hype

640
00:31:25,016 --> 00:31:25,783
and publicity

641
00:31:25,917 --> 00:31:27,085
ahead of the patient.

642
00:31:27,518 --> 00:31:28,353
His motives aren't pure.

643
00:31:28,353 --> 00:31:28,987
What do you want me to do?

644
00:31:31,656 --> 00:31:32,724
As long as you agree to operate,

645
00:31:32,924 --> 00:31:33,791
I can go with you

646
00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:34,492
to talk to Director Sheng.

647
00:31:34,626 --> 00:31:35,126
Say what?

648
00:31:35,693 --> 00:31:36,227
"Director Sheng,

649
00:31:36,294 --> 00:31:37,562
we suspect your motives aren't pure,

650
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:38,630
so don't do this surgery.

651
00:31:38,663 --> 00:31:39,364
Let Lin Yi do it"?

652
00:31:39,631 --> 00:31:40,164
Then how should we say it?

653
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:41,332
We can discuss it further.

654
00:31:42,867 --> 00:31:43,635
You know

655
00:31:43,968 --> 00:31:45,403
how much effort it took

656
00:31:45,603 --> 00:31:47,038
to restore Du Yan's will to live.

657
00:31:47,305 --> 00:31:48,439
I truly hope he receives

658
00:31:48,439 --> 00:31:50,074
the safest and most reliable treatment.

659
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:51,109
Like Xiaorui,

660
00:31:51,109 --> 00:31:51,943
he's a child who's had a very hard life.

661
00:31:51,943 --> 00:31:52,644
How is he like Xiaorui?

662
00:31:54,512 --> 00:31:55,480
How exactly is he like Xiaorui?

663
00:31:57,248 --> 00:31:58,016
They share a birthday.

664
00:31:58,950 --> 00:31:59,684
They're about the same age.

665
00:32:00,451 --> 00:32:01,753
Are you insisting I operate

666
00:32:01,786 --> 00:32:03,288
to make up for the regret

667
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:04,122
of not saving Xiaorui?

668
00:32:04,722 --> 00:32:05,690
That's not what I mean.

669
00:32:05,690 --> 00:32:06,791
He's not the same as Xiaorui.

670
00:32:10,328 --> 00:32:11,129
He's lying right there.

671
00:32:13,631 --> 00:32:14,432
Xiaorui is already dead.

672
00:32:19,837 --> 00:32:21,005
This surgery has nothing to do with me.

673
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:24,042
And I don't need this kind of redemption.

674
00:32:48,266 --> 00:32:49,167
Thank you, Director Sheng.

675
00:32:49,567 --> 00:32:50,802
Here's to the success

676
00:32:50,835 --> 00:32:51,736
of this operation.

677
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:52,637
A pleasure working together.

678
00:32:53,104 --> 00:32:54,005
It's a great honor

679
00:32:54,172 --> 00:32:55,173
that you will be the one

680
00:32:55,273 --> 00:32:56,107
to launch our product's first case in China.

681
00:32:56,441 --> 00:32:57,575
We truly feel privileged.

682
00:32:58,009 --> 00:33:00,011
When the time comes, we'll also

683
00:33:00,511 --> 00:33:01,446
build publicity for our product,

684
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:02,413
for Dongli Cardiac Surgery,

685
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:04,515
and for you, Director Sheng.

686
00:33:05,083 --> 00:33:06,651
I remember you're also

687
00:33:06,651 --> 00:33:08,453
a strong candidate

688
00:33:08,586 --> 00:33:09,454
for chair of the Heart Failure Committee

689
00:33:09,454 --> 00:33:11,122
of the next Dongjiang Medical Association.

690
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:13,224
With this operation

691
00:33:13,224 --> 00:33:14,192
strengthening your record,

692
00:33:14,392 --> 00:33:15,893
your victory should be assured.

693
00:33:20,198 --> 00:33:21,799
These empty titles may matter

694
00:33:21,799 --> 00:33:22,400
to you,

695
00:33:22,867 --> 00:33:24,202
but for Director Sheng,

696
00:33:24,435 --> 00:33:25,870
the surgery

697
00:33:25,970 --> 00:33:27,005
and the patient always come first.

698
00:33:27,305 --> 00:33:28,172
Of course. Of course.

699
00:33:28,439 --> 00:33:30,074
We certainly hope

700
00:33:30,208 --> 00:33:32,043
for what's best for the patient, Director Sheng,

701
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:33,544
and for all of us.

702
00:33:33,611 --> 00:33:34,679
Exactly. Exactly.

703
00:33:34,746 --> 00:33:35,013
Come.

704
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:36,114
A toast to Director Sheng.

705
00:33:36,347 --> 00:33:36,881
Come, let's toast Director Sheng.

706
00:33:36,881 --> 00:33:37,949
To Director Sheng.

707
00:33:39,951 --> 00:33:40,318
Director.

708
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:41,152
Mr. Qin.

709
00:33:45,423 --> 00:33:46,024
Lin Yi.

710
00:33:47,492 --> 00:33:48,826
I still want to talk to you.

711
00:33:49,994 --> 00:33:50,795
Another day.

712
00:33:54,432 --> 00:33:55,733
I have surgeries all day tomorrow.

713
00:34:15,253 --> 00:34:15,653
Zhang Zhen.

714
00:34:17,355 --> 00:34:17,722
Director.

715
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:22,493
You look well.

716
00:34:23,127 --> 00:34:23,428
How is it?

717
00:34:23,628 --> 00:34:24,796
Are you settling into the new company?

718
00:34:25,363 --> 00:34:25,863
Pretty well.

719
00:34:26,330 --> 00:34:27,532
It really took some time

720
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:28,066
to adjust.

721
00:34:29,367 --> 00:34:29,967
I ordered you coffee.

722
00:34:30,968 --> 00:34:32,003
Insurance claims review

723
00:34:32,303 --> 00:34:34,005
is basically doing a doctor's work

724
00:34:34,038 --> 00:34:35,072
from a different perspective.

725
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,207
My clinical experience

726
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:37,241
and academic background

727
00:34:37,442 --> 00:34:38,376
are useful too.

728
00:34:39,243 --> 00:34:39,811
That's good.

729
00:34:40,445 --> 00:34:41,045
Thank you, Director.

730
00:34:42,079 --> 00:34:43,347
And please thank Manager Ouyang for me.

731
00:34:44,315 --> 00:34:45,349
I'll cherish the opportunity

732
00:34:45,683 --> 00:34:46,184
and work hard.

733
00:34:46,951 --> 00:34:47,385
Do your best.

734
00:34:50,688 --> 00:34:51,756
The company has just started.

735
00:34:51,989 --> 00:34:52,690
Keep it up.

736
00:34:53,324 --> 00:34:54,358
If you run into any other difficulties,

737
00:34:54,592 --> 00:34:55,326
you have to tell me.

738
00:34:55,893 --> 00:34:56,794
No more being polite with me.

739
00:34:57,762 --> 00:34:58,329
It's okay.

740
00:34:59,197 --> 00:35:00,364
I've recovered now.

741
00:35:02,366 --> 00:35:02,967
Enough about me.

742
00:35:03,568 --> 00:35:04,802
I actually asked you here today

743
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:07,105
because there's something else

744
00:35:07,171 --> 00:35:07,872
I wanted to tell you.

745
00:35:08,639 --> 00:35:09,106
What is it?

746
00:35:11,309 --> 00:35:12,510
I only heard this

747
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:13,478
through other people.

748
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:15,346
I don't know whether it's true. Just hear me out.

749
00:35:16,447 --> 00:35:18,149
A group of us

750
00:35:18,549 --> 00:35:19,684
went to Europe together, right?

751
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:21,519
The senior directors

752
00:35:21,686 --> 00:35:23,187
didn't accept cash gifts directly.

753
00:35:23,554 --> 00:35:24,388
But I heard

754
00:35:25,022 --> 00:35:26,124
accounts were opened overseas

755
00:35:26,357 --> 00:35:27,725
for some directors.

756
00:35:28,159 --> 00:35:29,627
Future product kickbacks

757
00:35:29,694 --> 00:35:30,495
would be transferred directly

758
00:35:30,561 --> 00:35:31,529
into those offshore accounts.

759
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:33,231
The accounts

760
00:35:33,331 --> 00:35:34,398
aren't under the directors' names,

761
00:35:34,632 --> 00:35:35,466
but the funds inside

762
00:35:35,566 --> 00:35:36,834
can be remotely controlled by them.

763
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:39,203
Remotely controlled?

764
00:35:39,770 --> 00:35:41,105
For overseas spending,

765
00:35:41,606 --> 00:35:42,840
children's tuition, property purchases,

766
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:43,841
international medical care,

767
00:35:44,175 --> 00:35:45,209
insurance, and so on.

768
00:35:45,877 --> 00:35:47,245
And if they need

769
00:35:47,411 --> 00:35:48,613
to move the money back,

770
00:35:49,146 --> 00:35:50,414
they can probably find a pretext.

771
00:35:56,053 --> 00:35:56,754
Which directors?

772
00:36:02,193 --> 00:36:02,693
Either

773
00:36:03,728 --> 00:36:05,463
directors with purchasing authority,

774
00:36:06,430 --> 00:36:07,632
or people like

775
00:36:08,232 --> 00:36:09,200
Director Lin,

776
00:36:10,234 --> 00:36:11,068
who exclusively handle difficult, critical,

777
00:36:11,102 --> 00:36:12,470
high-end procedures.

778
00:36:12,803 --> 00:36:14,205
They decide which products get used.

779
00:36:14,906 --> 00:36:16,707
I don't really have evidence.

780
00:36:16,841 --> 00:36:17,842
And I don't want people thinking

781
00:36:17,842 --> 00:36:19,243
I'm making random accusations now.

782
00:36:19,644 --> 00:36:20,845
I've already suffered

783
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:22,079
such a major fall.

784
00:36:22,079 --> 00:36:22,346
I...

785
00:36:22,713 --> 00:36:24,115
I'm genuinely worried about Director Lin.

786
00:36:24,949 --> 00:36:25,483
Maybe

787
00:36:26,250 --> 00:36:28,152
you should verify it with him.

788
00:36:44,569 --> 00:36:45,403
I'm here to see Xiaoran.

789
00:36:46,237 --> 00:36:46,837
She isn't back yet.

790
00:36:47,238 --> 00:36:47,872
I'm here to see you.

791
00:36:52,443 --> 00:36:53,411
What do you want to say?

792
00:36:53,744 --> 00:36:54,612
Make it quick.

793
00:36:54,612 --> 00:36:55,346
I still need to go out.

794
00:36:57,014 --> 00:36:58,015
The offshore account—

795
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:00,985
it has nothing to do with you, right?

796
00:37:05,823 --> 00:37:06,591
Who told you?

797
00:37:08,125 --> 00:37:08,960
Zhang Zhen.

798
00:37:13,164 --> 00:37:14,398
Just tell me openly.

799
00:37:15,533 --> 00:37:16,601
Say you don't have one, and I'll believe you.

800
00:37:18,636 --> 00:37:19,003
I do.

801
00:37:20,371 --> 00:37:20,838
Director Lin.

802
00:37:21,372 --> 00:37:21,772
This

803
00:37:21,772 --> 00:37:23,074
is a small token of our appreciation.

804
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:23,774
We mainly wanted you to—

805
00:37:23,808 --> 00:37:24,475
I can't accept this.

806
00:37:24,775 --> 00:37:26,410
No, don't misunderstand.

807
00:37:27,144 --> 00:37:28,346
Business is business.

808
00:37:28,613 --> 00:37:29,614
Use our product

809
00:37:29,647 --> 00:37:30,414
when it's appropriate.

810
00:37:30,748 --> 00:37:31,315
If it isn't,

811
00:37:31,315 --> 00:37:32,750
we would never pressure you.

812
00:37:37,455 --> 00:37:38,155
Don't worry.

813
00:37:38,756 --> 00:37:40,725
We've considered everything for you.

814
00:37:41,325 --> 00:37:42,760
This is a bank account

815
00:37:42,793 --> 00:37:44,528
our company opened for you.

816
00:37:44,795 --> 00:37:45,596
The password is inside.

817
00:37:46,163 --> 00:37:47,431
It's not under your name.

818
00:37:47,999 --> 00:37:48,733
Please take it.

819
00:37:54,972 --> 00:37:55,673
Xiao Cheng, right?

820
00:37:56,474 --> 00:37:56,807
Yes.

821
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:00,211
I appreciate the gesture.

822
00:38:03,681 --> 00:38:04,015
All right.

823
00:38:05,082 --> 00:38:05,549
We'll talk later.

824
00:38:11,889 --> 00:38:12,823
Here's your bill.

825
00:38:13,991 --> 00:38:14,492
I'll pay by card.

826
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:35,813
Zhang Zhen really is something.

827
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:38,249
He fell into the water himself

828
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:39,450
and still insists on dragging someone down.

829
00:38:42,486 --> 00:38:42,987
Are you drinking or not?

830
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:52,029
What about the envelope?

831
00:38:53,431 --> 00:38:54,031
Did you return it?

832
00:38:56,467 --> 00:38:56,834
No.

833
00:38:59,103 --> 00:38:59,870
The envelope.

834
00:39:02,473 --> 00:39:03,641
The envelope.

835
00:39:07,244 --> 00:39:08,112
It's in the bag.

836
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:15,853
Here.

837
00:39:21,625 --> 00:39:22,560
Good thing you didn't open it.

838
00:39:24,128 --> 00:39:24,995
There's still time.

839
00:39:24,995 --> 00:39:25,663
Return it immediately.

840
00:39:30,601 --> 00:39:31,268
Why should I?

841
00:39:33,804 --> 00:39:34,672
What are you thinking?

842
00:39:37,241 --> 00:39:38,609
Do you understand

843
00:39:38,642 --> 00:39:39,110
what an offshore account means?

844
00:39:40,411 --> 00:39:41,445
Do you know how serious this is?

845
00:39:41,512 --> 00:39:42,413
How serious can it be?

846
00:39:43,047 --> 00:39:43,447
A warning?

847
00:39:44,648 --> 00:39:45,082
Dismissal?

848
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:47,852
At worst, I'll become another Zhang Zhen.

849
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:53,157
I'll return it for you.

850
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:53,924
Put it down.

851
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:01,866
I'll answer for my own actions.

852
00:40:01,932 --> 00:40:03,234
You don't have to clean up after me every time.

853
00:40:04,535 --> 00:40:05,403
Or are you planning to report me?

854
00:40:06,604 --> 00:40:07,605
If you want to ruin yourself,

855
00:40:07,605 --> 00:40:08,272
that's your business.

856
00:40:08,906 --> 00:40:09,440
But what you're doing

857
00:40:09,507 --> 00:40:10,441
will implicate Xiaoran.

858
00:40:10,641 --> 00:40:11,509
What happens between Fang Xiaoran and me

859
00:40:11,609 --> 00:40:12,309
is none of your business.

860
00:40:12,409 --> 00:40:13,043
How is it none of my business?

861
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:14,111
I know perfectly well

862
00:40:14,111 --> 00:40:15,012
what I've done.

863
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:15,813
What are you talking about?

864
00:40:17,314 --> 00:40:18,015
What account?

865
00:40:20,785 --> 00:40:21,085
Lin Yi.

866
00:40:21,085 --> 00:40:22,119
Did you take money you shouldn't have?

867
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:23,287
Return it immediately.

868
00:40:25,156 --> 00:40:25,623
I won't.

869
00:40:31,128 --> 00:40:31,796
That money is for you.

870
00:40:35,332 --> 00:40:36,066
If something happens

871
00:40:37,001 --> 00:40:37,835
in the future,

872
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:42,106
at least you'll have something left.

873
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,175
I don't need your money.

874
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:46,143
You're crossing a red line. Do you know that?

875
00:40:46,143 --> 00:40:46,877
Are you insane?

876
00:40:53,050 --> 00:40:53,350
Fine.

877
00:40:57,488 --> 00:40:58,322
I'm wrong again.

878
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:01,692
Everything I do is wrong,

879
00:41:01,725 --> 00:41:02,126
isn't it?

880
00:41:02,526 --> 00:41:03,694
I wanted to do the right thing too.

881
00:41:04,728 --> 00:41:06,430
I devoted myself to saving patients.

882
00:41:06,430 --> 00:41:06,931
And what happened?

883
00:41:09,767 --> 00:41:10,734
That donor heart

884
00:41:10,768 --> 00:41:11,669
went to Lu Dadong.

885
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:13,771
Xiaorui collapsed at home.

886
00:41:13,971 --> 00:41:14,972
I put him in the ambulance.

887
00:41:15,039 --> 00:41:15,706
In the general ICU,

888
00:41:15,706 --> 00:41:16,874
I watched him die

889
00:41:16,974 --> 00:41:17,708
right in front of me, unable to do anything.

890
00:41:17,975 --> 00:41:18,809
So that was the right choice?

891
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:20,744
That is how it ended for me.

892
00:41:22,847 --> 00:41:23,414
We know

893
00:41:23,447 --> 00:41:24,915
you need time to process it

894
00:41:24,915 --> 00:41:25,483
and adjust.

895
00:41:25,749 --> 00:41:26,717
But you can't remain

896
00:41:26,750 --> 00:41:27,685
trapped in it forever.

897
00:41:28,686 --> 00:41:29,253
Xiaorui's death

898
00:41:29,253 --> 00:41:30,454
hurt us just as much.

899
00:41:30,487 --> 00:41:31,088
It's not the same.

900
00:41:33,591 --> 00:41:34,758
You have a brother. You have a sister.

901
00:41:34,758 --> 00:41:35,392
You don't understand me.

902
00:41:35,559 --> 00:41:36,293
You don't know

903
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:37,428
how dark my world is.

904
00:41:37,561 --> 00:41:38,128
You don't know

905
00:41:38,195 --> 00:41:38,829
the kind of life

906
00:41:38,896 --> 00:41:39,997
I face every day.

907
00:41:44,802 --> 00:41:45,569
You don't understand me at all.

908
00:41:49,073 --> 00:41:49,406
Right.

909
00:41:50,708 --> 00:41:51,408
It really isn't the same.

910
00:41:54,211 --> 00:41:55,446
We've always treated you as family.

911
00:41:56,914 --> 00:41:58,349
And I want to become your family.

912
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:00,518
What about you?

913
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:10,494
My entire family is dead.

914
00:42:33,517 --> 00:42:33,951
Lin Yi.

915
00:42:36,353 --> 00:42:37,488
Do you really believe that?
